<br>
Recently, I have seen many posts and tales of account hacks and scams.  I have seen a few of my close personal friends lose everything they have worked for, and on a more personal level, things that i helped work for.  Midnight Fury even recently recieved a post on our public board with a link to a website which by use of javascripts and security holes in explorer can and does install a trojan virus.  I am certain this was in attempt to gain access to some high level accounts and gear.  <br>
<br>
People are forced to change their passwords regularly and live in fear that someone may gain access to their accounts.  With VI's security policy, I would be screwed if I lost my password.  I no longer pay on the same credit card I started with, I no longer have any records of what that card number was, and I no longer have my original CD keys.  As i sat here thinking of that possibility, I thought about who is ultimately responsible for affecting MY life in regards to the security of everything i have worked hard to obtain over the past 3 years and it points to you - the consumer.<br>
<br>
Your lack of respect, dedication, and even self-worth that would entice you to purchase someone elses work and/or glory with real money has paved the way for a new breed of EQ players and guilds.  Your need to have something you  can't obtain, lack the drive to obtain, and generally don't deserve has fueled a new form of EQ economy - the almighty dollar.  A big business now exists for lazy, worthless, f uckheads who now have a full-time revenue figuring out ways to rob us of our most precious resource - time - because of your pathetic mentality that you will be more accepted or respected because of an item or character.  <br>
<br>
As your friend's accounts get plucked off one by one, and the posts of others misery and lost time they chose to devote to this game is stolen....<br>
<br>
As your screen fills with pop-up ads and javascript web pages that can potentially open a hole for someone more intelligent and driven than you to take your private information off of your computer....<br>
<br>
As your in-game experiences are in any way delayed, frustrating, or ruined due to an encounter with the beloved ebay farmer.....  Remember that you are to blame.  You are the root of the problem.  You are a worthless piece of s hit.<br>
<br>
